main event: An unidentified object was observed on radar falling to the ground in Clear Lake, Maine on 5 October 1960, but no physical evidence was found.
interesting points: The radar tracked a potential unidentified object falling but lost it below the horizon,The original witness heard a sound described as a thud but did not see the object fall,Investigators found no physical evidence or holes where the object reportedly fell,There were no eyewitnesses to confirm the object's descent,The case suggests the sound may have come from building materials rather than an actual incident.
witness description: the witness reported a thud sound but did not see anything fall
